	<div class="col-md-6"><a href="https://www.dkorinteriors.com/portfolio-item/designed-volumes/" target="_blank"><img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Minimalist-OpenConcept.jpg"></a></div>
	<div class="col-md-6"><a href="http://www.ctagroup.com/portfolio/private-residence-whitefish-mt/" target="_blank"><img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Minimalist-WhitefishLR.jpg"></a></div>
</div>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Minimalist interiors thrive on basic simplicity. The coordination between minimal but functional is crucial. Making up a large part of its composition are the furnishings featured within. These must be able to multi-task while remaining less complex in design. However comfort is still a priority; to achieve a clean look opt for fitted and tailored furnishings, especially those that are cushioned. Utilizing clean, flowing lines throughout helps to create that sense of spaciousness minimalist interiors are known for. Purity in design is essential, as each design element must have the integrity to stand alone. Investing in quality furnishings allows the design to come together more naturally. Restraint must be used though when it comes to mixing furnishing styles. Choosing a classic style such as a Windsor chair will add a timeless essence to the design, but bringing more than one piece of such stature will end up creating confusion rather than cohesion.</p>			
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center"><a href="http://www.darcihether.com/portfolio/city/park-avenue-south-nyc/#&gid=1&pid=5" target="_blank"><img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Minimalist-ParkAveBR.jpg"></a></div>	
<div class="spacer"></div>	

<p>As with any interior design, details make the difference between an ordinary space and an extraordinary one. Minimalist interiors are so striking because of their lack of extraneous clutter. Everything has a rightful place, which contributes to their clean environments. A lack of excess keeps these interiors streamlined and spacious. However, the extremity of this design may also lend it a cold, uninviting aura. Bring life into the space by allowing certain elements to become a focal point. These small personalized touches contribute an individual sense of style without overpowering the design.</p>
<div class="spacer"></div>
